The paper deals with action recognition in videos using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves designing a new type of convolutional kernel, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also involves experimentation with different kernel sizes and their impact on performance, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
